Title: Abandoned Duties
Description: Defeat the former Watcher Antonio Guerra, find any mementos at his camp, and put his soul to rest. Then report back to Magistrate Wallace in the Mourningdale Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Sorry, I shouldn't pour my heart out to a stranger. It's just that Tony… our Watcher was our champion.\n\nI'm trying to be strong, but I just can't. Not with Tony still… wandering around out there, Lost.
InProgressResponse: Please, do try to be gentle, but of course, do what must be done. \n\nTony was a good Watcher, and a good man. His soul deserves rest.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: His spyglass…? Oh dear, he… he kept it so clean. He was a man of such integrity.\n\nIt was a gift, you know, this spyglass. I still remember the day I gave it to him. We were so happy then…

Title: Tears of a Wraith
Description: Defeat Spirits at Stephen's Claim to Collect Teardrop Gems. Then report back to Artificer Wrightson in the Mourningdale Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Bad? More like non-existent! I don't craft things so they can rot on the shelf!\n\nArt is only useful when it's being used, when it's being purchased!
InProgressResponse: Legend suggests the Teardrop Gems are a crystallization of tears from the weeping Wraiths that haunt the mine. \n\nBut I don't buy it. Do ghosts even have tear ducts? I think not.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, exquisite! The gems are virtually colorless, almost haunting. \n\nMaybe all that wailing in the mines really does lead to better quality gems?

Title: Excommunicated Gold
Description: Recover the gold medallions from Padre Nuñez at his Mansion. Then report back to Artificer Wrightson in the Mourningdale Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It's nice to make your acquaintance - I sense that you take a longterm perspective, unlike the others here.\n\nIf you're interested in another venture - I know where we can score some gold medallions.
InProgressResponse: Padre Nuñez was both eccentric and dangerous.\n\nTake care when you visit the Mansion.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, yes! These medallions will melt down quite nicely. Nuñez cost this settlement so much.\n\nIt's only fair that his treasures should now go to support us in our hour of need.

Title: Chasing Waterfalls
Description: Clear Weeper enemies from Porridgepot. Then report back to Constable Bayles in the Mourningdale Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm afraid my time as Constable nears an end. I can't solve Mourningdale's problems any more.\n\nMy body appears middle-aged, but I am actually one of the oldest people on the island.
InProgressResponse: I need a place where I can just go and sit quietly, undisturbed.\n\nThe cottage and the waterfall seem to be calling my name.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Tell me, how was it out in Porridgepot? \n\nIt seems silly coming from one as old as I am, but I actually feel a little excited about the place.

Title: Après Moi, le Déluge
Description: Investigate the ruins in the Flooded Plains, and return found artifacts to Gildon in Mourningdale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Wait... shifting dimensions bring something into focus. It's YOU! \n\nIn your eyes, I see it clearly. The waters rise and drown the settlement. I too am drowned, pulled under…
InProgressResponse: Standing on the edge of the water, we see a reflection of ourselves in its surface.\n\nAnd that is what obscures the truth that lies beneath.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, the orbs... do you hear them? The whispers? \n\nThey speak in a language I do not know, but the words bring a tear to my eye, nonetheless.

Title: Road to Truth
Description: Defeat Novaguard foot soldiers in the lookouts along the Ancient Road, and give their armor scraps to Gildon in Mourningdale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I see fragments… the stones of a road, north and south.\n\nThe stones are sealed with an undying light, azoth… and the Guardians walk the road in an endless journey.
InProgressResponse: The tattered cloth and the dull gold of the lookouts' armor are but fragments of their past.\n\nIt's that past I need to grasp.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Armor in tatters, they still stand guard and protect the road. \n\nAn endless duty, but perhaps one not chosen. Yes, not a duty, but a shackle. They are not free, and they never were.

Title: Ancient Truths, Ancient Lies
Description: Defeat Fineseer foot soldiers while climbing to the top of Vela, and show its treasure to Gildon in Mourningdale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Indeed, you are bound too, {playerName}. You bring blinding light to blinding darkness. \n\nA Watchtower, ancient and powerful, is your next destination. Vela. A treasure you seek, at its peak.
InProgressResponse: The watchers in the tower, what is it they watched for?\n\nIs it the same now as it was then?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: My sight grows stronger as you appear, and what did you find...  a spyglass? An object that gives a view across Mourningdale.\n\nBut through this spyglass, I see not across space, but across time…

Title: Razor to the Beard
Description: Defeat Musslebeard and the Seasong pirates in his charge. Then report back to Magistrate Wallace in Mourningdale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Exactly. Watcher Guerra had observed a new level of organization, of purpose, among the Lost Pirates.\n\nThe infamous Musslebeard leads them as he did in life. They're making preparations even now.
InProgressResponse: Tony's Journal suggest he secretly attacked Musslebeard's cove several times.\n\nIt seems he was defeated one time too many. I wish I had known.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Did you do the deed, then? Did you avenge my Antonio and destroy Musslebeard?\n\nIt's like a salve to my embattled soul. Honestly, until now, I seriously considered joining him.

Title: Corrupted Energy
Description: Defeat the Redeyes and destroy Spewspitter's emblem in New Balefire, then return to Gildon in Mourningdale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I believe so - I believe it was that which assaulted my mind with a chorus of ancient screams.\n\nBut you have restored a measure of quiet and the clarity. I see now what must be done.
InProgressResponse: The Corruption cannot be permitted to spread here.\n\nIt is up to you to stop it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You succeeded! That Corruption Totem was blinding and pained me in the deepest parts of my soul.\n\n It projected a timeless promise of violence and conquest... when you destroyed it, I saw its truth.

Title: Southward March
Description: Investigate key locations to the north that have been taken by the Wardogs. Then report back to Magistrate Wallace in Mourningdale.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Of course, you helped her recover her vision, and I am grateful for that.\n\nYou've not only avenged Tony, but taken his place. That's why I must ask your help again, to save us from this new menace.
InProgressResponse: The Wardogs appeared in our territory even before the Shattered Mountain erupted.\n\nI have no idea what they might be planning now.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hmm. You recovered ore and… compasses? I wonder what these are for?\n\nThe ore suggests they may be mining and stockpiling weapons, but compasses? That makes no sense.

Title: Crashing the Wake
Description: The Mourningdale settlement has been struck by tragedy and is in disarray. Constable Bayles will fill you in.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It's a tragic state of affairs. Our much-adored Watcher, Antonio Guerra, has fallen and become one of the Lost. \n\nAngharad Wallace is taking it particularly hard, the poor woman... her heart is shattered to pieces.
InProgressResponse: If you want to help us, speak to Fletcher.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You spoke to the Constable? Good. Bayles is a kind soul, but his mind falters.\n\nHonestly, I don't have the answers either, but I wonder if an outsider might offer a fresh perspective.

Title: Ode to Aeternum
Description: Pierre Auguste would like new tales of Aeternum, but is too timid to travel himself. Write a collection of odes to the scenic locations described in Pierre's guidebook.
PlayerPrompt: "This place can be both beautiful and terrifying."
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
That's what I'm told. I even bought a guidebook! 

I admit though, I'm a coward. Quelle folie... 

It must be frightful to die.
InProgressResponse: Have you visited the places in my guidebook? \n\nI'm eager to hear of your experiences out in the world!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Ah, you're back! 

I'm burning with anticipation to read your contributions! 

Leilani's stories are wonderful, but she's retired. I yearn for new tales!

Title: Stone Cold Secrets
Description: Follow Leilani's clues, written on your map, to complete her last adventure and find three lost artifacts of Ancient construction.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I finally encountered a cliff I could not climb. Old age. \n\nI can't fight like I used to and my bones ache more each day. My adventuring days are pau.
InProgressResponse: Are you taking a rest? In-between tasks? \n\nDo let me know if you've found whatever secrets are locked inside those monuments.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Well look at this, Pierre! Our adventurer returns! 

That's a confident swagger if I've ever seen one. 

Tell me what you've discovered!

Title: The Last Mystery
Description: Travel to three locations marked on your map and investigate whether Leilani's key can be used at each.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: They fit together into a larger artifact. \n\nIt's got markings that I believe correspond to some Ancient sites I visited in my adventuring days.
InProgressResponse: Have you tested that artifact yet? I'm sure it all means something. \n\nWhat mysteries still lie hidden out there?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Look, Pierre! Our stalwart returns! \n\nTell us, was it a key? What mysteries did it unlock?

Title: A Toast to Adventure
Description: Bring Leilani's Special Order to the Bartender in the Mourningdale Tavern.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Ae! A toast to adventure. 

Faced with adversity, you still rise to the occasion. 

Reminds me of myself, when I was young and wild.
InProgressResponse: Hurry up and bring my order to the bartender, then! \n\nDon't hang about!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What's this? Another order from that woman upstairs? \n\nI thought I just saw her friend leaving…

Title: Amateur Adventurer
Description: Follow the trail of clues to find where Pierre has gone.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
My friends! 

Your stories of valor and verve have inspired me! 

Soon I will be back to regale you with tales of my own adventure to the north!
InProgressResponse: This is the note left by Pierre when he set out for adventure.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh thank the heavens, it's you! \n\nI've been stuck here for days! C’est la galère!

Title: Song of the Sea
Description: Find the Captain's lost Shanty Book and Hurdy-Gurdy.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Nothing like that. This be a tragic tale. 

Music’s me soul, y'see. But me crewmates never fancied me shanties. Blamed 'em, in fact, for us having run aground on this rock. 

So they stole me hurdy-gurdy an' threw me out!
InProgressResponse:
I don't feel like meself these days. 

Me music be the only thing left to cling to out here. 

Without it, I may just slip away like th' rest o' them…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Dancing dolphins! Me hurdy-gurdy! Ye've found her! 

An' me shanties as well! 

I don't know how I could repay ye.

Title: Village Champion
Description: Recover Lerato's Heirloom armor and sword from the Corrupted in Ceremony and return them to her at the crossroads.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Who else? 

My father was our town's defender. He died fighting, and the Corrupted took his weapon and his armor. 

I can't move on until I get them back.
InProgressResponse: My father fought them in the streets, but for every one he struck down, five more would take their place. \n\nI must avenge him, but first I need to get his armor back.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
You're back! 

And with my father's armor as well! I'd recognize it anywhere! 

You've done me and my father a great kindness.

Title: Malign Dominion
Description: Find and destroy Malign Nodes at each of three Corrupt checkpoints along the road, then return to Harunobu at the crossroads. Some of these nodes are out of reach, you may need to bring a ranged weapon.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
They must be! 

I may be just a hog farmer from Hibbotsfeld, but I recognize purpose when I see it! 

They've locked down the northern road like a Corrupted constabulary!
InProgressResponse:
Ah! Stay back! 

Oh, it's you again. Have you seen what those Corrupted are up to on the roads? 

I'm beginning to worry I'll never see my hogs again!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Yah! You have got to stop startling me like that! 

Did you see what those Corrupted are doing? 

Did you destroy their Malign Nodes?

Title: Makin' Bacon
Description: Harvest Mourning Pigs in Hibbotsfeld for Harunobu and return them to him at the crossroads.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Hogs! 

I'm a hog farmer. Always have been. 

I've got nothing left now! If only I had a way to get some of my precious pork…
InProgressResponse: Well? Did you go to my farm? \n\nI'd do it myself, but I'm just a hog farmer.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Oh, that's Hibbotsfeld pork if I've ever seen it. 

Look at that marbling! 

It's all in my special regimen of 2 quarts of beer and a massage for each pig, every day!

Title: Soul Music
Description: Clear away the Withered around the Ancient Head so that Jan Jaansen can better hear the mysterious voice.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Are you sure? It's right there, playing at the edge of my hearing. 

But those damned Withered are so loud. I can't hear myself think! 

If only they were gone.
InProgressResponse:
I almost had it for a moment! 

If only those Withered were driven away… 

It's something like a poem…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
I heard it! For but a moment it was clear as the dawn! 

A song of epic proportions, a song of… 

Well I'm not exactly sure yet, but gracious, am I inspired to figure it out!

Title: Following the Bard's Song
Description: Search the coastal roads for Jan Jaansen
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Thanks for the inspiration! 

Here's to the brave soul that helped me to find my way on the roads north of the Settlement! 
You're a real muse. I may write a song just about your great deeds! 

There are still heroes in this world! Let's cross paths again, perhaps in the north? 

J. Jaansen
InProgressResponse: (Jan Jaansen wrote this note. \n\nCould it be about you?)
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It's as though you heard me calling for you from so far away.

Title: New Perspective
Description: Get to the end of Presage Pier and look for inspiration for the next stanza of Jan's epic.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Worthy of ballads, I'm sure! Care to take on another task for me? \n\nThe muse compells…
InProgressResponse:
It all started with that voice, the one in the Ancient Head. 

Are you sure you couldn't hear it? 

It was like a poem, but it was so bewitching. It moves me!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You are indeed a heroic sort, aren't you? \n\nTell me then, what did you find?

Title: Harmonic Resonance
Description: Follow Jan Jaansen's inspiration to the location foretold in Jan's inspiration.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
But it's in the air, it's all around us! 

I can hear it ringing. 

It's telling me that the secret is at the lighthouse.
InProgressResponse: Jan seems lost in her thoughts. \n\nShe hums a haunting tune.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: (You are oddly compelled to touch the Ancient Sculpture, and to your surprise, contact with the smoothed stone reveals a cosmic sense of music. \n\nA wordless vision of vastness, and of escape.)

Title: Welcome to Mourningdale
Description: Find Harunobu, recently of Hibbotsfeld.
PlayerPrompt: "The Corruption problem up north is bad!"
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
So I've heard. 

More and more people falling through here lost their livelihoods. 

Some lost worse!
InProgressResponse:
Have you checked in with those newcomers yet?

Don't want them feeling left out after all that's happened to them.

Let's show them some Mourningdale hospitality, eh?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Hey it's {PlayerName}!

Great to see you again. Want to try some of this pork?

The facilities here are top notch!

Title: The People in the Neighborhood
Description: Bring a sample of Harunobu's roast pork to Lerato.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
I was at the brink of despair for a time there. 

But, that woman from the crossroads, Lerato? 

She was kind enough to travel here with me.
InProgressResponse:
Hey{PlayerName}! 

Get that meat to Lerato while it's still hot! 

It gets a little greasy when it cools off.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh hello, what have you brought me? \n\nAh, bless that Harunobu, he is so kind to me.

Title: Seasoned Adventurer
Description: Race Pierre home to the Mourningdale Settlement
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
I intend to! 

I'll just take a moment to catch my breath, then I'll make haste back to my nice warm stool. 

Let's make a race of it! Bet I get back before you!
InProgressResponse:
I've just tightened up my laces and checked my pockets. 

I'll be ready for the road soon. 

What will Leilani think of us when we get back and share our tale?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Well, well! You made it back! 

I thought you might have been faster than me, but here we are! 

Those bluish shrines really make travel convenient, non?
